## Commands

```bash
go run ./cmd/api
gofmt -l .
go test ./...
go vet ./...
go build ./cmd/api
```

## CI

GitHub Actions workflow is defined at `.github/workflows/ci.yml`.

It checks formatting with `gofmt`, runs `go vet ./...`, runs `go test ./...`, and builds `./cmd/api`.

## Docker

```bash
docker build -f deployments/docker/Dockerfile -t {{ .AppName }} .
docker compose -f deployments/docker/docker-compose.yml up --build
```

Docker Compose includes the API service, MySQL, and Redis for local development.

## Configuration

Configuration is read from environment variables into `internal/config.Config`.

```text
APP_NAME
APP_ENV
HTTP_ADDR
DB_DRIVER
DB_DSN
DB_ENABLE_NESTED_TRANSACTION
REDIS_ADDR
REDIS_PASSWORD
REDIS_DB
LOG_LEVEL
```

MySQL support is registered through `github.com/go-sql-driver/mysql`. Leave `DB_DSN` empty to run without a database connection, or set `DB_DRIVER=mysql` and a MySQL DSN to enable startup-time connection checks.

Repository integration tests generated by `gos make:repository` use the `integration` build tag and `TEST_DATABASE_DSN`.

```bash
docker compose -f deployments/docker/docker-compose.test.yml up -d
TEST_DATABASE_DSN='root:password@tcp(127.0.0.1:3307)/{{ .AppName }}_test?parseTime=true' go test -tags=integration ./internal/infrastructure/persistence/mysql
```

Without `TEST_DATABASE_DSN`, generated repository integration tests are skipped.

## API contract

The default HTTP contract starts at `api/openapi.yaml`.

Update the OpenAPI file before implementing new HTTP handlers, then keep request and response DTOs aligned with that contract.

## Dependency assembly

Application dependencies are assembled in `internal/app/assembly.go`.

Use that file to wire repositories, usecases, handlers, queues, storage clients, and other infrastructure implementations with explicit constructors.

`Makefile` is included as an optional convenience only. The project does not require a local `make` command.
